  "texts": [
    "This result suggests that in chondrocytes, Clec11a may also bind to integrin a11 to promote the activation of Wnt signaling.",
    "The upstream-downstream relationship among Wnt signaling, Clec11a, and its receptor integrin a11 should be further explored to identify additional roles of Clec11a in skeletal system diseases.",
    "Clec11a may be a promoter of chondrocyte proliferation and longitudinal bone growth in juvenile mice (Figure 4).",
    "However, its effect on chondrocyte proliferation varies among different age groups.",
    "For example, it was reported that Clec11a does not work in mice at the ages of 4 and 14 days."
